to come from the main bulge\nprogenitor. {Nevertheless, it still} has a low probability of being formed from\nan accreted event because its age is uncertain and because of the combined\n[Mg/Mn] [Al/Fe] abundance. Its relatively low metallicity with respect to old\nand moderately metal-poor inner Galaxy clusters may suggest a low-metallicity\nfloor for globular clusters that formed in-situ in the early Galactic bulge.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 12 Jan 2023 18:59:59 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 18 Jan 2023 18:10:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-08"}
