ies. We discuss in detail the physical consequences\nof this and contrast it to emergent ${0}$-form symmetries, which are typically\nnot exact. Lastly, we show that at finite temperature, emergent 1-form\nsymmetries are no longer exact, but emergent $p$-form symmetries with ${p\\geq\n2}$ remain exact.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 12 Jan 2023 19:16:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 2 Mar 2023 08:22:33 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 15 May 2023 15:17:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-16"}
